  (1,'Mid-level PHP Developer','Responsibilities:\r\n\r\nAssisting in the development of our Zend Framework based client facing online applications as well as improving our legacy vanilla PHP based internal FX trading support systems.\r\n\r\n    Leading the design and subsequent development of application components from both a front-end and back-end perspective.\r\n    Taking ownership of large portions of existing applications and managing ongoing improvement and enhancement of these sections to meet business needs.\r\n    Writing documentation for the portions of applications you are responsible for.\r\n    Identifying potential areas of risk and suggesting mitigating actions.\r\n    Assisting in the planning and estimation of the development team’s work.\r\n\r\nSkills and experience required:\r\n\r\nExcellent knowledge of:\r\n\r\n    Object Oriented PHP5\r\n    (X)HTML & CSS\r\n\r\nGood knowledge of:\r\n\r\n    MVC frameworks, especially Zend or Symfony\r\n    MySQL\r\n    Cross browser compatibility and accessibility\r\n    Code repositories\r\n\r\nBasic knowledge of:\r\n\r\n    Windows and Linux CLI\r\n    Bug tracking tools\r\n\r\nEssential experience:\r\n\r\n    An ability to rapidly and effectively understand and translate business requirements into technical solutions\r\n    Proven skill in developing and managing maintainable code-bases\r\n    Knowledge and experience of cross-browser issues\r\n    Experience of working in an environment where products have to be delivered to specific time-scales\r\n    Self-motivated with good organisational skills in order to work to challenging deadlines\r\n    Experience of supporting, modifying and maintaining systems and code developed by others\r\n\r\nYou will get:\r\n\r\n    A fun working environment based in central London\r\n    An international, talented team of co-workers\r\n    Access to company funded training, development and certification\r\n    Free tea, coffee, fruit, breakfast and a Friday beer fridge\r\n    Relaxed dress code',1),
  (2,'С# Developer','responsibilities\r\n\r\n     Development of the business logic of products in the field of virtualization (Backup & Replication, Monitoring, Reporting)\r\n     Development of a new, development and support of existing functionality\r\n     The implementation of a functional on the level of small parts of the product\r\n     Participation in the development of the architecture of the product components\r\n\r\nrequirements\r\n\r\n     Higher technical education\r\n     Experience in developing commercial software for 2 years\r\n     Good knowledge of C # programming language\r\n     A good understanding of the platform Windows (.NET, Win API)\r\n     Good understanding of data structures and algorithms\r\n     Understanding the principles of design and development of software\r\n     The desire to learn and improve in the field of software development\r\n     Technical English (reading technical documentation and literature)\r\n\r\nadditional skills\r\n\r\n     Experience in developing the architecture of the product components\r\n     Good knowledge of SQL, T-SQL and experience with MS SQL\r\n     Experience with the virtual infrastructure (VMware vSphere, Microsoft Hyper-V)\r\n\r\nTerms\r\n\r\n     Interesting and promising projects\r\n     Work in a stable, dynamic company\r\n     Opportunity for professional growth\r\n     Wages on the basis of interviews\r\n     Clearance for TC, white salary\r\n     Holidays 28 days\r\n     Health insurance VHI\r\n     Partially paid fitness\r\n     The opportunity to join our football team',5),
  (3,'C++ Developer - C / C++ UNIX','C++ Developer / C++ Software Engineer (C / C++ UNIX). Global financial institution is seeking a passionate C++ Developer to design and develop highly complex distributed systems that push financial data to a global user base. This an excellent opportunity for a C / C++ Developer with the right skillset to gain valuable experience in the highly competitive finance sector.\r\n\r\nAs a C++ Developer you will be working on high performance servers to develop multi-threaded systems used by tens of thousands of traders around the world, requiring 24/7 availability. You will be working in a small, agile team that encourages knowledge sharing to deliver world class quality code that is efficient and scalable.\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n'' C / C++ development skills on UNIX\r\n'' Multi-threaded programming\r\n'' Ability to apply technology to solve real world business problems\r\n'' Experienced across the full software development lifecycle\r\n'' Degree educated, 2.1 or above\r\n'' Desirable: project management / technical leadership\r\n\r\nAs a C++ Developer you can expect to earn a highly competitive salary (to 55k), bonus and benefits.\r\n\r\nSend your CV or call for a confidential discussion about this and other current C++ Developer / C++ Software Engineer (C / C++ UNIX) positions. ',5),
  (4,'Java Developer','Our User Services team is looking for a Software Engineer to help drive brand new and exciting user engagement and CRM features across the Skyscanner product.\r\n\r\nWere looking for a talented and motivated Software Engineer who designs and delivers new functionality and scalable systems to a high degree of quality. As part of the agile, cross-functional team, you will be working on both client and server side.\r\n\r\nBased out of our modern central Edinburgh and/or Glasgow office you will have the opportunity to make a large and immediate impact on the software used by millions of people around the world every day.\r\n\r\nYoull enjoy working in a fast paced environment and be able to take on technical challenges with a positive attitude. You should be comfortable working as part of a team and you exhibit team-driven values and behaviours in both your personal attributes and how you approach your work.\r\n\r\nWhat we''re looking for:\r\n\r\n-A keen problem-solver with the desire and interest to solve difficult technical challenges\r\n-A good team player with a can-do attitude\r\n-Takes responsibility for delivery and getting things out to production\r\n-Understands and has an interest in the techniques of best practice in software delivery\r\n\r\nDesired Skills and Experience:\r\n\r\n-Experience in developing rich web applications using HTML, CSS, JavaScript\r\n-Strong experience in JAVA development\r\n-Good understanding of the HTTP protocol\r\n-Experience with testing frameworks and continuous integration\r\n-Strong object oriented design knowledge and SOLID principles\r\n\r\nOther skills and exposure which will add weight to your application:\r\n\r\n-Previous experience implementing User Engagement or CRM technologies\r\n-Exposure to NoSQL databases\r\n-Mobile web, performance optimisation and CDNs\r\n-Understanding of SOA and experience with queuing systems\r\n-Previous exposure to .NET or Python\r\n-Experience with JavaScript MV* frameworks (Backbone/Angular/Ember/Knockout)\r\n-Embrace TDD, agile practises and have knowledge of web testing frameworks such as Selenium\r\n\r\nTo visit our website and apply for this role please click the APPLY button.',5),
  (5,'Java Engineer','WHAT WE NEED IN A NUTSHELL\r\n\r\nWe are transforming our platform and want you to be part of it; as a result we''re looking for a number of experienced Java developers at a range of levels to work as part of our technical team at notonthehighstreet.com in Richmond. As an engineer, you will work closely with a cross-functional team composed of technical, creative, business development, user experience and marketing professionals following strong Agile principles.\r\n\r\nWHAT THE ROLE ENTAILS\r\n\r\nReporting into the Development Manager, some of the things you will get involved in are:\r\n\r\n-Writing, testing and maintaining quality code\r\n-Working with a small, empowered cross-functional team to deliver business value\r\n-Helping to maintain and improve our best practices\r\n-Providing support for other team members through code review and pairing\r\n-Be part of our success and make a difference\r\n\r\nTHE TYPE OF PERSON WE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nBecoming part of a diverse team, it''s essential that you have excellent communication skills (fluent English is a must), are well organised, detailed and accurate, can work quickly to tight deadlines and have the ability to collaborate with junior or non-technical members of the wider notonthehighstreet.com team.\r\n\r\nTHE KEY SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE WE NEED\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate will be from an e-commerce background with experience building high availability backend services using strong agile development practices.\r\n\r\n-Java, Spring, Spring Boot, Cassandra, RabbitMQ, JavaScript and JS frameworks, REST, Cloud Technologies, NOSQL\r\n-Keen software engineering approach and very good object-oriented design ability\r\n-Desire to work closely with the business, learn new things and teach others\r\n-Ability to take ownership of a project or issue, analyse it and solve problems not faced before\r\n-Mobile web and/or native development\r\n-TDD and object-oriented design skills\r\n-Experience with agile development methodologies\r\n-Champion of modern development practices and tools, eg Continuous Delivery with Jenkins, Source Control with Git, BDD with Cucumber\r\n-Previous e-commerce experience would also be beneficial\r\n-Website and user experience design awareness would be an advantage\r\n-You''ll need a technical background, with a strong Computer Science, Software Engineering or similar degree.\r\n\r\nIn return, we offer you a dynamic, fast moving, rapidly growing environment, where we value creativity and innovation, technical excellence and responsibility/ownership.\r\n\r\nIF THIS IS THE RIGHT FIT FOR YOU, APPLY NOW!\r\n\r\nWe''d love to hear about what you can do for us and how you can add value to our people and our business.\r\n\r\nTo apply, please visit our website by clicking the APPLY button. ',5),
  (6,'Functional Test Manager','31,150-49,052 per annum (Includes Market Forces Rate allowance of up to 10,952 depending on skills and experience plus benefits)\r\n\r\nAbout the role\r\n\r\nONS has Technology at its core and is looking for an experienced Functional Test Manager to join its talented team of over 340 IT professionals.\r\n\r\nAre you an experienced Test Manager, working in an agile arena, with experience in the software development life cycle (SDLC) and test tools that support it - Rational Jazz suite - in particular Quality Manager and Functional Tester?\r\n\r\nAre you a proven leader able to communicate fluently to all stakeholders and peers, who is able to direct staff effectively and efficiently to deliver tested software within agreed timescales to meet quality and value business benefits?\r\n\r\nAre you interested in playing a vital role in delivering trusted statistics used by hundreds of organisations to deliver better services to millions of people across the country? Statistics that you see in the news every day.\r\n\r\nIf you are, then the ONS may have the right new challenge for you! We are looking for experienced Functional Test Manager to join our talented team of IT professionals delivering large, complex digital solutions that help Britain make better decisions.\r\n\r\nStatistics are vital to every imaginable area of our daily lives, and vital to the production and dissemination of these statistics is robust, effective, cutting-edge technology. At ONS, IT is key to delivering innovative, interactive, highly flexible digital services that will delight our users, driving modernisation and streamlining all of our operations. Our IT professionals put us at the forefront of government digitalisation and data visualisation. This is an exciting time to join the team, as ONS recognises the demand and develops its digital capabilities. An IT career at ONS is an opportunity not to be missed!\r\n\r\nAbout ONS\r\n\r\nFor the Office for National Statistics, people count. Whether that''s the people across the country whose lives our work helps to shape, or the people who work here, producing vital statistics that informs decision making in our society and economy. We achieve results by investing in the people who work with us, rewarding their contribution and enabling a better work/life balance. We''re a welcoming and friendly community of professionals, we respect each other and we''re very social. We''ve some impressive on-site facilities too, including a gym, coffee shop, even a hairdresser.\r\n\r\nApply\r\n\r\nFor more information about us and our jobs please click the apply button. We are also holding two IT Recruitment Open Days in September, for professionals to find out about the exciting IT job opportunities we can offer. The open days are on: 11 September 2014 from 2pm, ONS Newport and 25 September 2014 from 2pm, ONS Titchfield. To find out more, please click on the ''IT Careers at ONS'' button above. ',3),
  (7,'Senior Test Engineer - Selenium / Agile','About Kainos:\r\n\r\nKainos are 50th in the Sunday Times 100 Best Companies to Work for, we provide digital technology solutions that enable companies to work smarter, faster, better, and we''ve been doing this successfully for more than 26 years. We employ over 500 people and have offices in the UK, Ireland and Poland.\r\n\r\nOur clients are predominantly in the Public, Healthcare and Financial Services sectors, and include well-known global organisations and large government departments. We pride ourselves on our people; they are knowledgeable, enthusiastic and have a work ethic that our clients tell us is unique and we are looking for more!\r\n\r\nMain Responsibilities:\r\n\r\n-Responsible for performing a range of system and specialist verification and validation tasks.\r\n-Responsible for the testing of relatively complex solutions using agile or traditional methodologies.\r\n-Will provide essential input into requirements capture, test planning and the capture of test metrics.\r\n-Will research outside of their normal test activities, take an active part in test process improvement and actively share knowledge to others.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Ideal Candidate will have:\r\n\r\n-A minimum of 3 years commercial experience in a testing role.\r\n-Experience of using Selenium and associated technologies\r\n-Experience of testing in two or more specialist areas and expert in at least one area.\r\n-Sound understanding of different delivery methodologies (E.g., Agile, Waterfall, V- Model)\r\n-Comfortable with testing in an agile environment.\r\n-Ability to create and implement an appropriate test strategy for a project, regardless of the delivery methodology that is being used.\r\n-Capable of producing workable test estimates and have the ability to deliver to these estimates.\r\n-Experience in test design from documented requirements and the ability to identify and manage undocumented requirements.\r\n-Sound understanding of the use of test metrics to provide accurate, meaningful, reporting.\r\n-Sound understanding of techniques for ensuring test coverage and traceability.\r\n-Experience in assessing, prioritising, and managing incidents through to closure.\r\n-Sound understanding of test management and defect tracking tools and good practice in the use of these tools.\r\n-Demonstrate a high level of technical awareness and a sound understanding of software architectures.\r\n-Demonstrable awareness of business environments into which solutions have been delivered.\r\n-Sound understanding and application of quality practices as applied to software testing.\r\n-Can recognize and flag issues outside area of own expertise or responsibility to team leader or manager, as appropriate.\r\n-Ability to communicate with various stakeholders (both technical and non-technical).\r\n-Ability to work well within a team setting, but also capable of working independently with minimal supervision.\r\n-Capable of supervising test staff during project phases as required.\r\n-Capable of working directly with customer to gain acceptance of the software.\r\n-Ability to mentor less experienced team members and lead by example in both technical and non-technical aspects of the job.\r\n',3),
  (8,'Software Tester','We are one of the leading UK Drupal CMS companies, known for a great team, great work and great clients. We work with a range of enterprise companies to transform their businesses through open source technology and agile working methodology. We have a strong culture centered around delivering quality code, working agile and having fun in the process. Our mission is to build the best UK drupal company that transforms organizations through technology. We need you to achieve this.\r\n\r\nYou are a highly experienced tester with a real passion for ensuring quality standards are met and only the best possible work goes out of the door at the end of the day. You''ll ideally have a good knowledge of Drupal and related best practices in order to help the whole team achieve the high calibre of work we are known for. You''ll have a long track record of working on enterprise level development projects within an Agile environment.\r\n\r\nYou''ll be comfortable with all forms of testing from load and performance to automated and unit. With your confidence from years of experience you''ll be happy taking on a key role within our often complex and large projects.\r\n\r\nKey accountabilities:\r\n-Producing test plans with the developers and PMs.\r\n-Produce test criteria against user stories in collaboration with product owner & business analysts/PM''s.\r\n-Ensuring ''definition of done'' testing criteria are met.\r\n-Managing test suites for projects to ensure standards are maintained.\r\n-Work closely with product owners and project teams to balance budget and thorough testing.\r\n-Clear communication with clients and teams.\r\n-Ensuring agreed levels of quality are achieved.\r\n-Support team members and clients where training is needed.\r\n\r\nEssential:\r\n-Substantial web / software testing experience.\r\n-Good knowledge of Jenkins, Selenium and other testing tools.\r\n-Proven experience of owning and managing the testing of large web based tools.\r\n-Dedication to quality and web standards.\r\n-A passion for best practice and pro-active in bringing in new ways of working.\r\n-Great communication skills and a proactive can-do attitude.\r\n-Experience working on enterprise agile / scrum projects.\r\n-A university degree, preferably software engineering or related.\r\n\r\nDesirable:\r\n-Knowledge of Drupal and its best practices.\r\n-Public contributions to open source projects (send us your GitHub ID, D.O ID).\r\n-Experience of presenting at conferences, camps and meet-ups.\r\n\r\nBenefits:\r\n-Salary: very competitive.\r\n-25 days paid holiday per year + public holidays.\r\n-Generous training allowance and research and development time.\r\n-Drupal cons and camps.\r\n-Regular office massages.\r\n-Your choice of setup (normally 2 x 24'' monitors, Mac or Ubuntu, Aeron chair).\r\n-Plenty of team lunches, good coffee, snacks and a nice place to work.\r\n-Company fun plan - go karting, cinema, theatre, bowling, archery, etc.\r\n-Company trip (France for a week).\r\n-Potential for flexi-time and working from home after 6 months.\r\n\r\nPlease send a CV and a covering email explaining why you would like to work with us by clicking the APPLY button.\r\n\r\nWe do not discriminate by age, gender, race, sexual-orientation, disability, or Mac / PC preference.\r\n\r\nWe can only accept applications from candidates with the legal right to work in the UK.\r\n\r\nStrictly no recruiters.',3),
  (9,'Lead Developer (SO) – Java or Scala','Come and join HMRC''s vibrant, new Digital Delivery Centre in Newcastle, where the needs of our customers are at the heart of everything we do. Using agile methods and the latest technology, you''ll be right at the forefront of building revolutionary new digital services that will be used by millions, changing forever how individuals, businesses and agents deal with their tax affairs\r\n\r\nIn HMRC we offer attractive benefits, good career prospects and a commitment to support your continued professional development, including regular development reviews and access to learning opportunities '' both on the job and more formal learning.\r\n\r\nTravel to other offices may also be expected from time to time.\r\n\r\nUnder the direction of product managers, scrum masters and technical leads, you''ll build develop, test and deploy outstanding digital services for millions of users. Building prototypes, writing tests, codes and documentations, implementing RESTful APIs, JSON ensuring continuous integration, providing ''second-line'' support and occasional ''on-call'' support - your time with us will be busy and rewarding. Experience in Java is a must, and additional Scala experience is highly beneficial. Test Driven Development (TDD) and automated testing is important to how we work. You will also act as the most senior developer in the team, where your extensive development and agile experience will help mentor, influence and ensure stories are developed and planned within the team.\r\n\r\nFor this role you will need:\r\n\r\n-A solid background in Java or Scala Development;\r\n-Experience working in an agile/scrum development environment;\r\n-Team leading experience;\r\n-Experience in developing digital and web solutions;\r\n-Experience in developing and using Open Source technologies such as MongoDB, NoSQL, Github, Jenkins, Ruby, Scala, Play framework, RESTful and JSON highly beneficial.\r\n\r\nTo find out more information about the job and how to apply online please click on the apply now button.\r\n\r\nClosing date: first closing date for recruitment campaign is 30th September 2014, but advert to remain open. ',5),
  (10,'Senior User Experience Designer','Research is looking for a talented, enthusiastic Senior User Experience Designer. The company provides News and Funding opportunities for researchers and academics across most of the UK''s universities and institutions across the world. Research also provides new and innovative ways for institutions and enterprise to collaborate and work together. While staying true to it''s roots in journalism, policy and funding opportunities for research, the collaborative networking side to the company begins to expand Research''s offer as its technology becomes recognised and sought after beyond universities.\r\n\r\nThe successful candidate will apply well-rounded and expert design skills to user flows, usability, and application interactions. The role requires a thorough understanding of interaction design principles and best practices, along with an understanding of how visual and interaction design work together to create world-class user experiences.\r\n\r\nRequired Skills & Experience;\r\n\r\n- 5+ years working as a UX Designer, Interaction Designer or similar role\r\n- Experience working in a multi-disciplinary design role\r\n- The ability to articulate and communicate design routes, whether one on one or to an audience\r\n- Proficiency with HTML/CSS/JavaScript, Adobe creative suite and wireframing software such as OmniGraffle or Sketch\r\n- Deep knowledge of the UX design process\r\n- Experience in design research, analyzing user flows, wireframing, and producing professional UX specification\r\n- Results-driven, able to initiate and lead projects; working autonomously and multi-tasking in a dynamic, fast paced environment\r\n- An impressive portfolio demonstrating a wealth of experience. This should include at least one project lifecycle, from wireframes to implementation\r\n- Outstanding communication skills '' both written and verbal\r\n- An exceptional eye for detail and the drive to consistently produce outstanding work\r\n- Experience working in agile project lifecycles\r\n- Experience in live style guides or pattern libraries and UI frameworks\r\n- A background in visual design, graphic design and brand communications should also be part of this candidate''s skill-set\r\n\r\nResponsibilities;\r\n\r\n- Working closely with the Development Team using a design process based that consists of fast prototypical iteration, testing and development for quality interface and application design delivery for a robust and efficient framework\r\n- Working as closely with the Marketing Team to deliver high impact, on-brand and engaging brand experiences both on and offline\r\n- You will be responsible for the full design lifecycle '' from wireframes and prototypes to fully realised mock-ups and html implementation too.\r\n- Working iteratively: regularly gathering feedback from users, stakeholders and customers\r\n- Defining and creating style guides and resource libraries\r\n\r\nNice to Have;\r\n\r\n- The ability to realise mock-ups in html\r\n- Experience working in a team based in various locations around the world\r\n- A presence in the global UX community (A personal blog, industry related twitter etc...)\r\n\r\nEducation;\r\n\r\n- Bachelors Degree / Human Computer Interaction degree (or equivalent in a design related subject)',2),
  (11,'Scrum UI Developer','Scrum UI Developer - Urgent - Warrington - UI, JQuery, JS - 30k!\r\n\r\nUI, JQuery, JavaScript, Ember, REST, Ajax, HTML, Experience, Scrum.\r\n\r\nScrum UI Developer - An exciting new opportunity has arisen for a Scrum UI Developer to join an award winning, industry-leading client of ours based in Warrington. This is a fantastic opportunity to become a key member a talented Scrum Development team, implementing high-quality UI code for a range of products.\r\n\r\nIn order to be successful for this role, you must have at least 3 years of commercial software development experience in addition to a number of the following:\r\n-Demonstrable experience of using JQuery and JavaScript MV frameworks (Ember advantageous)\r\n-Understanding of REST, websockets and Ajax\r\n-Experience of responsive design\r\n-Experience of working in an Agile delivery environment\r\n-A Bachelor Degree in Computer Science or equivalent required.\r\n\r\nMy client is paying a salary of 30,000 for this UI Developer vacancy with benefits. They are looking to move quickly so do not miss out - please submit a copy of your CV for immediate consideration!\r\n\r\nUI, JQuery, JavaScript, Ember, REST, Ajax, HTML, Experience, Scrum.',2),
  (12,'UI Development Engineer : JavaScript','UI Development Engineer : JavaScript, Web : 3 to 6 month Contract : Edinburgh\r\n\r\nAbrecco wish to recruit, on behalf of our client, a contract UI Development Engineer. Our client is looking for the best UI Developers available to work on business critical projects. The successful applicants will need to demonstrate technical expertise of working with the latest bleeding edge technologies in the development of feature rich UI?s for mobile, tablet and desktop devices. To be considered for this truly outstanding opportunity you should possess the following skills and experience:\r\nEssential:\r\n- Expert UI Development experience\r\n- Ability to develop requirements from design ideas to fully integrated UI solutions\r\n- Visionary approach to finding technical solutions to technical challenges\r\n- Ability to work with the broader team in the development of UI / UX Solutions\r\n- Expert JavaScript Development skills\r\n- In depth knowledge of MVC (Backbone.js, Angular.js, Ember.js etc.)\r\n- Expert CSS skills\r\n\r\nTo be considered for this role please forward your up to date CV together with details of your availability and desired day rate.',2),
  (13,'Information Security Analyst ','PruHealth is an award winning, dynamic and vibrant health insurance provider, with a ground-breaking vision for the future, where individuals are enabled to succeed and are rewarded and recognised for their contribution to our business.\r\n\r\nOur CORE PURPOSE is to make people healthier and to enhance and protect their lives. From people to products and processes, we aspire to deliver on our purpose in everything we do.\r\n\r\nReporting to the Senior Information Security Manager, the role is to assist the Senior Information Security Manager in ensuring that, across the organisation, information assets are adequately protected and that appropriate controls and mitigating actions are in place to manage identified information security risks.\r\n\r\nAs a member of the Information Security Team, you will provide advice and guidance to the organisation on information security best practice. Provide information security training and awareness for all staff.\r\n\r\nYou will possess a track record of successful information security analysis roles within Financial Services sector and a sound understanding of security standards, data protection and regulatory compliance (e.g. Financial Services Authority and Information Commissioners Office)\r\n\r\nHave previous experience of developing and implementing information security policies and procedures and hold a degree educated in an IT or technology related discipline, (ISC)² Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP) or Certified Information Security Auditor (CISA) ITIL v2 or v3 Foundation Certificate\r\n\r\nWorking for PruHealth, you''ll experience an exciting mix of creativity and innovation, within a framework of challenging objectives and a passion for delivering the best. We think work should be fun and sociable, and we want our people to get the most out of every day.\r\n\r\nOur people are chosen for their skills, knowledge, enthusiasm and attitude but above all, their belief that anything can be achieved.',4),
  (14,'IT Service Desk Analyst ','This is an opportunity to progress your IT career, in a business that''s committed to every employee''s development.\r\n\r\nIT at Bidwells\r\n\r\nThis role is based in the 15 strong IT department at Bidwells, one of the country''s leading independent property consultancies. We have almost 500 staff working across 12 offices in England and Scotland - IT plays a vital role in supporting our business and connecting our people. That means we''re a busy, customer-focused IT team that''s always looking to increase our skills and expertise.\r\n\r\nKey responsibilities\r\n\r\nYou''ll be assisting in the day-to-day operational work of the IT Service Desk team. The main focus is providing business facing IT support over the telephone, via email, or in person. We want you to take ownership of issues and see them from origin to resolution '' using your initiative to prioritise and manage different issues. You will also maintain and install computer hardware and software systems. You''ll quickly become a valued member of the team by offering great customer service, especially to people from a non-technical background.\r\n\r\nYour profile\r\n\r\n-You need proven IT support experience in a Windows environment, and strong knowledge of Microsoft Office applications and operating systems. (Microsoft certification is preferred).\r\n-Familiar with working in business/user facing roles, you will have a proven record of resolving complex technical software issues and hardware issues on PCs, laptops, multi-function printers, mobile devices etc. Experience of liaising with 3rd party suppliers or support organisations is also a must.\r\n-You should also be a good communicator and team worker who keeps abreast of the latest technologies and is keen to take advantage of training and development opportunities.\r\n-You need a driving licence and own car for transport between offices.\r\n\r\nFor further details, please visit our website by clicking the APPLY button.\r\n\r\nClosing date: 24 September 2014 ',4),
  (15,'Analyst Team Leader','Use your analytical expertise to make a difference.\r\n\r\nPermanent and fixed-term opportunities available\r\n\r\nJoin us as an Analyst Team Leader and you''ll take on a role like no other, working with unique data and influencing decisions that help CQC to ensure England''s health and social care is safe and effective. You will join a highly ambitious analytics unit that aims to be at the cutting edge in the use of health and social care information.\r\n\r\nAs the independent regulator of health and adult social care in England, we make sure that hospitals, dentists, GPs, ambulances, care homes, and care-home agencies meet government standards of quality and safety. Our work touches the lives of everyone in the country '' and everything we do relies on effective analysis.\r\n\r\nTake this senior role, and you lead a team analysing data on the services used by millions of people. You''ll take a full and active role in our sociable environment, from allocating workloads and monitoring delivery, to developing the skills of individual team members. At the same time you could be designing systems, processes and tools for modelling, analysis and interpretation of data, or meeting with providers to explain our Intelligence products. It''s an excellent opportunity to take on high profile projects that you can get immersed in.\r\n\r\nIt''s likely you''re currently working as an analyst in the public sector, perhaps in a service that the CQC regulates, though you may also be a researcher or research assistant in academia. Degree qualified or equivalent, you will enjoy using spreadsheets and other data analytical tools to work out the best way to approach a task and present the data and findings. Above all, you''ll be keen to play an important role in the inspection of hospitals, GP practices or care homes to support improvements in the patient experience.',4),
  (16,'PHP Engineers / PHP Developers - PHP / Zend 2 / Doctrine','Here at Kainos, we are currently looking for a number of Senior PHP Engineers/PHP Developers to join our Bristol based team on a Contract basis.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for candidates with the following skill sets:\r\n\r\n-PHP\r\n-Zend Framework 2\r\n-Doctrine 2\r\n-GIT\r\n-Linux (CentOS)\r\n-Apache\r\n-MySQL\r\n-Agile development\r\n-PHP Unit\r\n-Continuous Integration\r\n-Code Reviews\r\n-HTML 5\r\n-JavaScript\r\n-JQuery\r\n\r\nThe Senior PHP Engineers will be responsible for the following:\r\n\r\n-You''ll be responsible for developing and testing software solutions as part of a team\r\n-You will be based on one of our great customer sites near Bristol - but don''t worry, we''ve a Bristol office too!\r\n-You''ll provide technical leadership and mentoring to other software engineers.\r\n-You will work from requirements or high-level design without the need for direct supervision.\r\n-You''ll be responsible for development and testing of major components for complex systems, using Agile methodologies.\r\n-You pride yourself on quality, you''ll promote quality software engineering techniques within the project team, such as code review, design review, reusability of code, refactoring, automated testing and the use of standards.\r\n\r\nAbout Kainos:\r\n\r\nKainos provides digital technology solutions that transform businesses, enabling companies to work smarter, faster, better. We have been operating successfully for more than 26 years and have a talented team of over 500 people, with offices in the UK, Ireland and Poland. We deliver exciting projects across Public, Healthcare and Financial Services sectors, where we build innovative systems and excellent services that are loved by their users.\r\n\r\nWe are proud to be one of the Sunday Times Best 100 Companies To Work For. We''re committed to our people''s development and actively encourage their engagement in the technology community and beyond. Working at Kainos surrounds you with enthusiastic and dedicated colleagues - everyone contributes to an environment which is built around flexibility, enjoying your work, continuous learning and active career progression.',1),
  (17,'PHP/ MySQL Web Developer','Knowledge and Experience required:\r\n\r\nThe successful candidate must possess good technical development, problem solving, organisation and communication skills. You should have experience of developing advanced web sites for third parties and will be able to demonstrate your programming skills and easily show the contributions you have made to existing web sites. You must be self motivated and able to work as part of a team to develop projects that are delivered on time and to budget.\r\n\r\nYour duties will include documenting through note taking and version control, editing and improving existing code, as well as taking ownership and helping to test, release, and maintain the code you write. Other duties include monitoring progress of clients websites against target delivery dates, completing quality checks and testing procedures, liaising with existing and prospective clients and other developers, as well as being able to support the existing development team and contribute to policy, procedure and product development.\r\n\r\nPerson Specification\r\n\r\nPart of what makes ICO3 successful are the highly motivated people who work here and their enthusiasm for online marketing. We recruit individuals whose honesty, integrity, initiative and a creative approach to problem solving. Our employees have a ''can do'' attitude. An inspiration to your colleagues, you''ll have passion and a commitment to getting things done while always placing the client at the centre.\r\n\r\nYou will have a minimum of:\r\n\r\nA suitable degree with demonstrable qualifications in computer programming and/or web development and at least two years experience in a web developer role working on your own or as part of a team using PHP and MYSQL.\r\n\r\nSkills required:\r\n\r\n- Good knowledge and experience with HTML/XHTML/CSS\r\n- Good knowledge and skill in PHP 5 and MySQL\r\n- Good Object Oriented PHP skills\r\n- Experience with JavaScript and common JavaScript libraries is highly recommended but not a requirement.\r\n- A suitable degree with demonstrable qualifications in computer programming and/or web development\r\n- At least two years experience in a web developer role working on your own or as part of a team using PHP and MYSQL\r\n- An impressive portfolio of client websites to which you have made a demonstrable contribution\r\n- Some knowledge and experience of the LINUX computing environment\r\n\r\nCompany Information:\r\n\r\nICO3 is a fast-growing and innovative Plymouth based E Commerce company providing our very best service to our clients. We are located at the Tamar Science Park in Plymouth and as of November 2011 employ 20 members of staff. The park provides free and extensive parking for staff and is easy to access from all parts of the city. Around the park are numerous cafes and restaurants; including an on site cafe and Dartmoor is only a short five minute drive.\r\n\r\nICO3 offers a professional, friendly and supportive environment within an open plan office free of discriminatory practices. Ambitious and hard working, you will join a robust in-house competencies development programme aiming at encouraging all employees to reach their full potential.\r\n\r\nBenefits: We have a strong cultural policy. We provide where possible flexible working hours, provide staff benefits (including a contribution to gym membership at the luxurious Devonshire Health Club) and an EMI employee reward scheme to rapidly acquire shares in the company and benefit in the long term from the company''s growth.\r\n\r\nOur Mission Statement: ICO3 provides an all embracing e-commerce strategy for businesses. We work in partnership with small businesses to help them sell online. Our ultimate aim is to give business owners complete reassurance - knowing that their day to day on-line business is being looked after and is growing. Our approach is to develop a long term partnership with business owners to a personalised specification. We evolve with the client to meet the ever growing and changing demands of their business. ',1),
  (18,'PHP Developer- Comic Relief- London- PHP/ HTML/ CSS/ JavaScript/','PHP Developer for Comic Relief- London-\r\n\r\nComic Relief are one of the best known charities based in the UK, with a vision of a just world, free from poverty.\r\n\r\nThey''re building up a team of PHP Developers to help see their vision through digitally, increasing the reach and outputs of their work, continuing to make the world a better place.\r\n\r\nYour role will include duties such as:\r\n\r\n*Maintain and update content and functionality of the Comic Relief websites / applications as directed by the Digital Production Manager.\r\n*Monitor performance of the Comic Relief web platform and liaise with DevOps to diagnose and rectify performance issues.\r\n*Ensure any tests required to keep the site to a high standard are in place.\r\n*Ensure the site is performant on both the back and front-end across all defined browsers and platforms.\r\n\r\nWe are interested in people with some of the following skills: PHP, Zend, Drupal, Codeigniter, Yii, HTML, CSS, Javascript, Magento\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in this PHP Developer role please click the ''apply now'' button below.',1),
